modules.description: This module encodes and decodes timestamps according to RFC 3164. It operates on `Ptime.t` values and string representations of timestamps. It is used to convert between a structured time value and the specific string format required by RFC 3164 syslog messages.

This module parses and unparses syslog messages according to RFC 3164, handling conversion between strings and structured message representations. It operates on data types including facility, severity, timestamp (Ptime.t), and message components like hostname, tag, and content. Concrete use cases include decoding raw syslog strings into structured messages for analysis and encoding structured messages into properly formatted strings for transmission to syslog daemons.
